# Teknovo GitHub Rule

## DO

- Check branch **before first edit**: `git branch --show-current`
- **Always create feature branches** for feature work: `git checkout -b feature/<scope>` (kebab-case)
- Commit on feature branch only; format: `feat(scope): description`
- Stage only relevant files â€” never secrets or `.env`
- Open PR for merge to `main`; human review required for protected branches
- Use worktrees for large parallel work: `.cursor/skills/superpowers/using-git-worktrees/`
- Use `gh` CLI for PRs, issues, checks when user requests GitHub operations

## DON'T

- **Never commit directly to `main` or `master`** for feature or user-project work
- Push or merge to `main` unless user explicitly requests
- Run destructive git commands (`push --force`, hard reset) without explicit user request
- Force-push to `main`/`master`
- Skip pre-commit hooks (`--no-verify`) unless user explicitly requests
- Commit unless user explicitly asks

## Pre-Edit Checklist

```bash
git branch --show-current
```

| Branch | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `main` / `master` | Create and checkout `feature/<scope>` |
| `feature/*` | Proceed |

